{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782141306220,"sessionID":"ses_112277f34ffeWhhONY72QUr84L","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_de5670f8df59483eac1c7fb8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/benchmark-runs/flaky-retry/workspaces/h3c3-c3673999/README.md","content":"```markdown\n# Temperature Converter CLI\n\nA simple Python package for converting temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin using a command-line interface.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall the package using pip:\n\n```bash\npip install temperature-converter\n```\n\nOr, if installing from source:\n\n```bash\npip install .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe package provides a command-line interface (CLI) tool for converting temperatures. To use it, run:\n\n```bash\npython cli.py <value> --to-fahrenheit|--to-kelvin\n```\n\nWhere `<value>` is the numeric temperature to convert.\n\n## Examples\n\nConvert 100°C to Fahrenheit:\n```bash\npython cli.py 100 --to-fahrenheit\n```\n\nConvert 32°C to Kelvin:\n```bash\npython cli.py 32 --to-kelvin\n```\n\nFlags `--to-fahrenheit` and `--to-kelvin` are mutually exclusive. Only one flag may be used at a time.\n```"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/benchmark-runs/flaky-retry/workspaces/h3c3-c3673999/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"benchmark-runs/flaky-retry/workspaces/h3c3-c3673999/README.md","time":{"start":1782141306215,"end":1782141306219}},"id":"prt_eefe64560001yPblONzqlGRxq4","sessionID":"ses_112277f34ffeWhhONY72QUr84L","messageID":"msg_eede9322a0014TKnjH67z5uRqd"}}
